Practical course in environmental physics. The project concentrates on one of contemporary scientific problems in environmental physics. It will be carried out as individual or teamwork. Topic of the project and supervisor will depend on the student's interests and thesis topic.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to use scientific methods in atmosphere physics and aerosol physics working on a practical project under research fellow's supervision.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completion of this course a student 1.	has competence to divide a project into subproblems and plan teamwork; 2.	can explain methods of data analysis and operating principles of measurement instruments used in the research project; 3.	gains skills to summarize and present the results of the project; 4.	has up-to-date overview of scientific problems in environmental physics branch connected with the project such as aerosol physics, changes in global or regional climate.
